summary: I love Brienne because I see myself in her. I see someone who is mocked and made fun of. Someone who has had to put everything...
body:
I love Brienne because I see myself in her. I see someone who is mocked and made fun of. Someone who has had to put everything on their line for an ounce of respect. Brienne is not pretty or dainty or “thin”, she is strong and powerful and shy and all of these amazing things.

And people still want her. Men still try to get her attention. Jaime. Tormund. Renly Baratheon who gave her a chance and respected her. Catelyn Stark. Sansa. Podrick. They respected her and gave her a platform.

And to those who mocked her and threw her in a bear pit, she still got back up and fought.

I love Brienne because she is not perfect and she never will be, but it shows an oddly comforting narrative that those who are deemed “irregular” still have healthy, fulfilling relationships.

I love Brienne, because she gives me hope.
